# Fix ocamlformat version alignment: local 0.28.1 vs CI 0.27.0

## Requirements

- Local dev environment uses ocamlformat 0.28.1 (specified in .ocamlformat `version` field)
- CI installs ocamlformat 0.27.0 (observed from CI setup)
- Any new .ml files formatted locally with 0.28.1 will fail `make fmt-check` in CI with 0.27.0
- Must resolve before any new OCaml files in P4.M1 are added to the repo

## Implementation

Option A (preferred): Align .ocamlformat to match CI version (downgrade local)
- Edit `.ocamlformat`: change `version = 0.28.1` to `version = 0.27.0`
- Re-run `make fmt` to reformat all files under the 0.27.0 rules
- Verify `make fmt-check` passes

Option B: Upgrade CI to 0.28.1
- Update CI yaml to install `ocamlformat.0.28.1` instead of current pinned version
- Verify CI fmt-check passes

Check: `grep -r ocamlformat .github/` and `cat .ocamlformat` to confirm current state before deciding.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `make fmt-check` passes both locally and in CI using the same ocamlformat version
- [ ] .ocamlformat `version` field matches the version installed in CI
- [ ] No formatting diff introduced on existing files (or intentional reformat committed cleanly)
